Just to let you all know, I can't post through the day because I have 
school, so I'll only be able to post early in the morning and late in the 
afternoon. Thanx.


* Iron Raptor almost fell over in relief that this new bot wasn't here to 
announce some attack on the Ark or some other heavy mission/problem she 
would have to deal with.
A smile crossed her lips as she stepped away from the scematic of the 
Cybertronian Fire(and Prowl) and towards the new Maximal, actually glad to 
meet Quake and how their force just grew a notch.
There were so many new bots coming to this world all the time, every new 
Maximal was more welcome then anything else.
Iron Raptor, however, wasn't quite as swamped with work as before and could 
actually afford this smile, the only other worry on her mind being that of 
the Ark.*

" Hot Rod, huh? Well, he told you to come to the right fembot."

* She held out her hand towards Quake, the smile on her face not wavering a 
bit.*

"Pleased to meet you, Quake. As you already know, my name's Iron 
Raptor...current Maximal Commander. And I would like to OFFICIALLY welcome 
you to the Maximals as well as the Beast Wars."

* But, just like Feline, she also wouldn't mind knowing just what sort of 
qualifacations this man had and how he could be of value to the Maximal 
force (skills).
Iron Raptor qhickly looked him over, from top to bottom. Noting everything 
about him that she could, and all that he hadn't told.*

" If you wouldn't mind, Quake? Could you please tell me a bit about 
yourself, skills and so on?"

* However, time was preciouse and she would have to make this a bit of a 
short introduction, knowing that she had much important things to deal with. 
The Ark, for one.
Though, already she was thinking of the just where she could send Quake to 
keep him busy, a job that didn't require too much if everything went right.
Protecting the Ark. He would go out with the repair and protection team she 
sent before she left for the Embassy.
Though, Kluster's news of the Ark cave in was none too assuring.*

" You see, I like to know as much about ever individual Maximal as I can and 
I also like to hear them speak themselves instead of having to look over a 
file every time. It makes them more familier with a few things and helps to 
break the ice.*
